{"id":"4937","name":"I'm Up! for Pushcut","tagline":"have Siri give you a briefing over your speaker system!","icon":"ios13 c4274264319 g59845","latest":"15887","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Hello all! so, if you dont know what I'm up is, then you are in for a treat.\nI'm Up is a shortcut for HomePod designed to give you a morning briefing the way that Google Assistant or Alexa can. but this version... shes real special</p>\n<p>this is a version that doesnt get triggered with Siri, but rather, using a Pushcut Automation Server, you can trigger it with a motion sensor in your home, a light switch, or whatever device you like using HomeKit!</p>\n<p>set up is simple, just answer each of the import questions, then configure the API in Home to work with your Pushcut Server.</p>\n<p>here are the actions:</p>\n<p>1 get a readout of all events you have going on today, as well as a time you should leave by and how long it will take to get there.</p>\n<p>2 get reminded about tomorrows all day events including Holidays and events such as Garbage Day if you added it. this feature is called Next Day.</p>\n<p>3 be told your reminders for the day</p>\n<p>4 play music</p>\n<p>5 change scenes and accessories</p>\n<p>6 get a weather readout!</p>\n<p>7 be told the temperature in your house</p>\n<p>8 get todays birthdays!</p>\n<p>due to the limitations of a fully automated system, features from I'm Up such as Starbucks or creating reminders about Next Day events are impossible at the moment.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - March 31, 2020, 8:24 p.m.</strong></p><p>Version 1.0 Release Notes<br>-  this is the official release! Enjoy your shiny new shortcut!<br><br>- Total Actions: #112<br>- Created on iOS 13.4<br>- Released at 2020-03-31</p>"}